%% ============================================================================
%% NU-AURA HRMS - Multi-Tenant Data Flow
%% TENANT ISOLATION ARCHITECTURE
%%
%% Render at: https://mermaid.live
%% ============================================================================

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as 👤 User<br/>(Tenant A)
    participant Browser as 🌐 Browser
    participant NextJS as Next.js Frontend
    participant API as Spring Boot API
    participant TenantFilter as Tenant Filter
    participant ThreadLocal as Tenant Context<br/>(ThreadLocal)
    participant Security as Security Service
    participant Redis as Redis Cache
    participant RLS as PostgreSQL<br/>Row-Level Security
    participant DB as Database

    %% Authentication Flow
    User->>Browser: Login with email/password
    Browser->>API: POST /api/auth/login
    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM users<br/>WHERE email = ?
    DB-->>API: User record (includes tenant_id)
    API->>API: Validate password (BCrypt)
    API->>Security: Load permissions for user
    Security->>Redis: GET user:permissions:{sessionId}
    Redis-->>Security: Cache miss
    Security->>DB: SELECT permissions<br/>WHERE tenant_id = ?
    DB-->>Security: Permissions list
    Security->>Redis: SET user:permissions:{sessionId}<br/>(TTL: 5 min)
    API->>API: Generate JWT<br/>(userId, tenantId, roles)
    API-->>Browser: JWT token (560 bytes)<br/>+ httpOnly cookie
    Browser-->>User: Login successful

    Note over Browser,DB: --- SUBSEQUENT API REQUESTS ---

    User->>Browser: Navigate to Employees page
    Browser->>NextJS: GET /employees
    NextJS->>API: GET /api/employees<br/>Authorization: Bearer {JWT}

    Note over API,ThreadLocal: TENANT ISOLATION ENFORCEMENT

    API->>TenantFilter: HTTP Request Filter
    TenantFilter->>TenantFilter: Extract JWT from header
    TenantFilter->>TenantFilter: Decode JWT<br/>Extract tenantId
    TenantFilter->>ThreadLocal: TenantContext.setCurrentTenant(tenantId)
    Note right of ThreadLocal: Tenant A UUID<br/>stored in ThreadLocal

    TenantFilter->>Security: Validate permissions
    Security->>Redis: GET user:permissions:{sessionId}
    Redis-->>Security: Cached permissions ✅
    Security-->>TenantFilter: Permission check passed

    TenantFilter->>API: Continue filter chain

    API->>RLS: Enable RLS for this connection
    Note right of RLS: SET app.current_tenant = 'tenant-A-uuid'

    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM employees<br/>-- RLS automatically adds:<br/>WHERE tenant_id = 'tenant-A-uuid'
    DB-->>API: Employees (Tenant A only)

    API->>ThreadLocal: TenantContext.clear()
    Note right of ThreadLocal: Clean up after request

    API-->>NextJS: JSON response<br/>(Tenant A employees)
    NextJS-->>Browser: Render employee list
    Browser-->>User: Display employees

    Note over User,DB: --- CROSS-TENANT ISOLATION TEST ---

    rect rgb(255, 200, 200)
        Note over User,DB: ⚠️ SECURITY SCENARIO: Malicious request with Tenant B ID

        User->>Browser: Attempt to access Tenant B data
        Browser->>API: GET /api/employees?tenantId=tenant-B-uuid<br/>Authorization: Bearer {JWT with tenant-A}

        API->>TenantFilter: HTTP Request Filter
        TenantFilter->>ThreadLocal: TenantContext.setCurrentTenant(tenant-A)
        Note right of ThreadLocal: JWT says Tenant A<br/>Query param ignored!

        API->>RLS: Enable RLS for Tenant A
        API->>DB: SELECT * FROM employees<br/>WHERE tenant_id = 'tenant-A-uuid'<br/>-- RLS enforced, query param ignored
        DB-->>API: Employees (Tenant A only) ✅

        API-->>Browser: JSON response<br/>(Tenant A employees, NOT Tenant B)
        Note right of API: ✅ Cross-tenant access blocked!
    end

    Note over User,DB: --- ASYNC OPERATION (VULNERABLE) ---

    rect rgb(255, 230, 200)
        Note over User,DB: ⚠️ ASYNC WEBHOOK DELIVERY (CURRENT ISSUE)

        User->>API: Trigger leave approval
        API->>ThreadLocal: TenantContext = Tenant A ✅
        API->>DB: UPDATE leave_requests<br/>SET status = 'APPROVED'
        API->>API: Publish LeaveApprovedEvent
        API->>API: @Async processWebhook()
        Note right of API: ⚠️ NEW THREAD SPAWNED

        Note over ThreadLocal: ❌ ThreadLocal lost!<br/>TenantContext.getCurrentTenant() = null

        API->>DB: SELECT webhook_url FROM webhooks<br/>-- NO TENANT FILTER! ⚠️
        DB-->>API: Webhook URL (ANY tenant!)
        API->>API: Send webhook ❌ FAILS

        Note right of API: FIX: Implement TaskDecorator<br/>to propagate ThreadLocal
    end
